Currently, when Public Signup is enabled, user's are automatically added to the Service Desk Project in the User's column of the Service Desk Customer Role. 

For instances with many thousands of public signup customers, it would be best if administrators had the option of adding these customers automatically to a group instead of just having them listed in the User's column of the Role. This way they could be managed better, and it would keep the Roles page more clean. If there are many thousands of customer's added to the Roles page, it will likely make this screen very long and unwieldy. 

It's understood that administrators can move these users to a group, but if there's public signup enabled, users are not likely to be added at once but instead gradually. This makes for an additional maintenance task for administrators to have to clean up the Roles page occasionally. It would be better if administrators could determine the group the public signup users are to be added to in advance rather than having to move them manually on a regular basis.

